The inside of the hospital is wrapped in silence.[p]
To the left there is a reception area, in which various papers are neatly placed on a shelf.[p]
Waiting benches are lined up along the back of this hall, and a television is pointed at them.[p]
I do not feel the presence of any patients, or even any people.[p]
Only faint light pours in through the windows from the cloudy sky.[p]
The hall is filled with a trace scent of alcohol, which penetrates my nose.[p]
I begin walking.[p]
After passing through the waiting room, I reach a long corridor.[p]
I open the door marked Examination Room.[p]


